    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the chicken is done, transfer to a clean board and shred it apart, using two forks – this technique is known as ‘pulling’</p><p>Add the <strong>pulled chicken</strong>, <strong>cooked pepper</strong> and <strong>drained farfalle</strong> to the peri peri sauce with a grind of <strong>black pepper </strong>and cook for 2-3 min or until the sauce begins to stick to the<strong> </strong>pasta – this is your <strong>peri peri chicken & pepper farfalle</strong></p><p>Tip: Add a splash of the starchy pasta water if it's looking a little dry</p>",
